{"title_page": "\u09a6\u0995\u09cd\u09b7\u09bf\u09a3 \u09a4\u09c7\u09a4\u09be\u09ad\u09c2\u09ae\u09bf \u09a8\u099c\u09b0 \u09ae\u09be\u09b9\u09ae\u09c1\u09a6 \u09ad\u09c2\u0981\u0987\u09af\u09bc\u09be\u09b0 \u09ac\u0982\u09b6\u09a7\u09b0", "text_new": "{{Infobox building\n| name                = Descendants of Nazar Mahmud Bhuiyan in South Tetabhumi \n| native_name         = South Tetabhumi Bhuiyan Bari / Old House \n| native_name_lang    = Bengali\n| former_names        = \n| alternate_names     =\n| status              = \n| image               = \n| image_alt           = \n| image_size          = \n| caption             = \n| relief              = \n| altitude            = \n| building_type       = Residence\n| architectural_style = \n| structural_system   = \n| material            = Bricks, Stone, and Rods\n| cost                = \n| ren_cost            = \n| owner               = Descendants of Nazar Mahmud Bhuiyan \n| current_tenants     = \n| landlord            = Nazar Mahmud Bhuiyan\n| location            = [[Brahmanpara Upazila]]\n| address             = South Tetabhumi\n| location_town       = [[Brahmanpara Upazila]], [[Cumilla District]]\n| location_country    = Bangladesh\n| iso_region          = \n| coordinates_display = \n| coordinates_format  = \n| latitude            = \n| longitude           = \n| latd                = \n| latm                = \n| lats                = \n| latNS               = \n| longd               = \n| longm               = \n| longs               = \n| longEW              = \n| coordinates         = \n| groundbreaking_date = \n| start_date          = \n| completion_date     = \n| opened_date         = \n| inauguration_date   = \n| relocated_date      = \n| renovation_date     = \n| closing_date        = \n| demolition_date     = \n| destruction_date    = \n| roof                = \n| top_floor           = \n| observatory         = \n| other_dimensions    = \n| floor_count         = \n| floor_area          = \n| seating_type        = \n| seating_capacity    = \n| elevator_count      = \n| grounds_area        = \n| rooms               = \n| parking             = \n| url                 = \n| embedded            = \n| references          = \n}}\n\nThe ''' South Tetabhumi Bhuiyan Bari ''' or old house was established by Nazar Mahmud Bhuiyan in about 1850 AD. It is a historical [[house]] of [[Brahmanpara Upazila]] in [[Comilla District]] of [[Bangladesh]]. The southern Tetabhumi of his descendants is known as \"Nazar Mahmud Bhuiyan's descendants\". He came from the then Lohagarh-Pargana, now Kalpash Brammanpara Bhuiyan Bari, and bought land from the owner of Zamindar Tareq Chowdhury's '''North Tetabhumi Zamindar Bari''' and settled there which belongs to Shashidal Union.\n\n\n\n==History==\nThis historic house was established by Nazar Mahmud Bhuiyan. Which is located in Brahmanpara Upazila of Comilla. Nazar Mahmud Bhuiyan, There were 4 brothers, Sugar Mahmud Bhuiyan, Sunny Mahmud Bhuiyan, Kabir Mahmud Bhuiyan. Nazar Mahmud Bhuiyan was a descendant of the Bara Bhuiyans of Bengal but no Bhuiyan could confirm this. He is probably a descendant of [[Ghiyasuddin Mahmud Shah]] and, according to many, a descendant of [[Isa Khan]]. Many people have this idea because of the marriage of the daughter of [[Isa Khan]], [[Ghiyasuddin Mahmud Shah]]. At present Kalpash is still known as Bhuiyan Bari in Brahmanpara. This Bhuiyan dynasty is still spread in [[Comilla]], [[Brahmanbaria]], [[Kishoreganj]] areas. However, the principle of hereditary customs is now extinct.\n\n==A series of descriptions of the descendants of Nazar Mahmud Bhuiyan==\n\n- [x] Nazar Mahmud Bhuiyan\n Nazar Mahmud Bhuiyan's five sons\n** Sony Uddin * ** Jony Uddin * ** Sadar Uddin * ** Kadar Uddin * ** Aftab Uddin *\n1. Sony Uddin:\n Soni Uddin has 9 sons and daughters\n** Hamid Ali * ** Minnat Ali * ** Jinnat Ali * ** Abid Ali * ** Meher Chan * ** Paher Chan * ** Chandra Ban * ** Unknown * ** Unknown *\n 1.4 6 sons and daughters of Abid Ali\n** Nurul Amin * ** Fariza Khatun * ** Harun Aur Rashid * ** Mofiza Khatun * ** Rukaiya * ** Mojibar Rahman *\n2. Johnny Uddin:\n Johnny Uddin has 7 sons and daughters\n** Yasin dealer * ** Heir * ** Mahmud Ali * ** Surat Ali Munshi * ** Unknown * ** Unknown * ** Unknown *\n 2.1 3 sons of Yasin Bepari\n** Mahmud Hossain * ** Ali Ahmed * ** Ali Akbar *\n 2.2 2 sons of Waris\n** Arsab Ali * ** Taleb Ali *\n 2.3 3 sons of Mahmud Ali\n** Chhayeb Ali * ** Tayyab Ali * ** Ayat Ali *\n 2.4 1 son of Surat Ali Munshi\n** Abdur Rahman *\n3. Sadar Uddin:\n 6 sons and daughters of Sadar Uddin\n** Torab Ali * ** Muharram Ali * ** Akmat Ali * ** Mushkat Ali * ** Surya Ban * ** Unknown * ** Unknown *\n 3.1 7 sons and daughters of Torab Ali\n** Majid * ** Abdul Aziz * ** Abdul Rahim * ** Faizunnesa * ** Nurjahan * ** Sabia *\n 3.2 6 sons and daughters of Muharram Ali\n** Montaz Sardar * ** Rafiqul Islam * ** Shahidul Islam * ** Tamuja * ** Ramuja * ** Rezia * ** Ketu *\n 3.3 6 sons and daughters of Akmat Ali\n** Sirajul Islam * ** Abdul Haq * ** Yunus * ** Yunus 2 * ** Abu Taher * ** Firoza * ** Khorsheda * ** Delwara *\n4. Kadar Uddin:\n Kadar Uddin has 2 sons\n** Nashar Uddin * ** Bashir Uddin *\n 4.1 6 sons and daughters of Nashar Uddin\n** Hajera Khatun * ** Moslem Uddin * ** Islam Uddin * ** Abdul Rashid * ** Md. Abdul Mannan * ** Asia Khatun *\n 7 sons and daughters of Moslem Uddin\n** Unknown * ** Ferdousi Rahman * ** Fazlul Quader * ** Habibur Rahman * * Khalilur Rahman * ** Khadija Rahman * Mushfiqur Rahman *\n 6 sons and daughters of Islam Uddin\n** Shirin Akhter * ** Kamal Hossain * ** Shamsur Nahar * ** Mostafa * * Taslima Akhter * ** Asma *\n 4 sons and daughters of Md. Abdul Mannan\n** Md. Rezaul Karim * ** Md. Ataul Karim * ** Fazle Rabbi Emon * ** Munta Sinha Meem *\n 4.2 6 sons and daughters of Bashir Uddin Uddin\n** Khwaja Ali * ** Mohsin * ** Jalal Uddin *\n5. Aftab Uddin:\n 4 daughters of Aftab Uddin\n** Unknown * ** Unknown * ** Unknown * ** Unknown *\n\