{"title_page": "Aahana Kumra", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Aahana Kumra \n| image              = Aahana Kumra on Day 2 of Lakme Fashion Week 2017.jpg\n| caption            = Aahana Kumra  2017\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1985|05|01}}<!-- Please cite a reliable source for date of birth -->\n| birth_place        = [[Lucknow]], [[Uttar Pradesh]], [[India]]<ref name=\"aah\">{{cite web|url=http://aahanakumra.com/index.php/me|title=Me - Aahana Kumra|website=aahanakumra.com|accessdate=11 February 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180212083456/http://aahanakumra.com/index.php/me/|archivedate=12 February 2018|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n| occupation         = {{hlist|[[Actress]]|[[Model (profession)|model]]}}\n| website            = {{url|aahanakumra.com}}\n}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2016}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2016}}\n\n'''Aahana Kumra''' (born 1 May 1985) is an Indian feature film, television, and theatre actress. Kumra is known for her small screen debut in Sony Entertainment Television's ''[[Yudh (TV series)|Yudh]]'' with [[Amitabh Bachchan]] and also her lead role in the TV series ''[[Agent Raghav - Crime Branch]]'' with Sharad Kelkar, followed by leading roles in a number of feature films.\n\n== Early life==\n\nKumra was born in a [[Hindu]] family in [[Lucknow]].<ref name=\"aah\"/>\n\n==Career==\nAahana Kumra, born and brought up in Lucknow, had an inclination towards acting since childhood when she began theatre roles. She is a graduate from Whistling Woods International School of Acting and started her career with advertisements and short films, appearing in advertisements for Garnier Fairness Cream, ICICI Bank, KFC, Reliance Internet and others.\nIn 2013, Kumra was cast in the television series ''[[Yudh (TV series)|Yudh]]'' - a 20-episode show starring Amitabh Bachchan in which Kumra plays the pivotal role of Bachchan's daughter. Later, she starred in ''[[Agent Raghav - Crime Branch]]'', a biweekly television crime thriller show, as the female lead Agent Trisha Dewan opposite Sharad Kelkar. Kumra won Best Actress Award at the Third Moida International Awards for her short film ''Siberia''. She made her Hindi feature film debut in ''[[Sona Spa]]'' in 2013,  and her Tulu feature film debut in 2015 in ''[[Kudla Cafe]]''. She hosted the Prokabbadi 2016 series. \n<ref>{{cite news|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/television/amitabh-bachchan-made-yudh-so-much-easier-aahana-kumra/|title=Amitabh Bachchan made \u2018Yudh\u2019 so much easier: Aahana Kumra|work=[[The Indian Express]]|agency=[[Press Trust of India]]|date=1 August 2014|accessdate=15 February 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150215072405/http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/television/amitabh-bachchan-made-yudh-so-much-easier-aahana-kumra/|archivedate=15 February 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://movies.ndtv.com/topic/aahana-kumra|title=Aahana Kumra|website=[[NDTV]] Movies|accessdate=15 February 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150215072023/http://movies.ndtv.com/topic/aahana-kumra|archivedate=15 February 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/aahana-kumra-was-not-nervous-to-work-with-amitabh-bachchan/489503-8-66.html|title=Aahana Kumra: Was not nervous to work with Amitabh Bachchan|agency=[[Press Trust of India]]|work=[[CNN-IBN]]|date=31 July 2014|accessdate=15 February 2015|url-status=bot: unknown|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140805035125/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/aahana-kumra-was-not-nervous-to-work-with-amitabh-bachchan/489503-8-66.html|archivedate=5 August 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/Aahana-Kumra-Gorging-on-dal-baati-churma-was-a-great-experience/articleshow/45512057.cms|title=Aahana Kumra: Gorging on dal baati churma was a great experience|first=Richa|last=Shukla|work=[[The Times of India]]|date=15 December 2014|accessdate=15 February 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141215231908/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/Aahana-Kumra-Gorging-on-dal-baati-churma-was-a-great-experience/articleshow/45512057.cms|archivedate=15 December 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.indiatvnews.com/entertainment/bollywood/amitabh-bachchan-s-yudh-actress-aahana-kumra-feels-fortunate-to-be-working-with-big-b-15390.html|title=Amitabh Bachchan's Yudh: Actress Aahana Kumra feels fortunate to be working with Big B|agency=[[Press Trust of India]]|work=[[India TV]]|date=2 July 2014|accessdate=15 February 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150215071019/http://www.indiatvnews.com/entertainment/bollywood/amitabh-bachchan-s-yudh-actress-aahana-kumra-feels-fortunate-to-be-working-with-big-b-15390.html|archivedate=15 February 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mid-day.com/articles/aahana-kumras-dream-to-work-with-big-b-comes-true/15418176|title=Aahana Kumra's dream to work with Big B comes true|agency=[[Indo-Asian News Service]]|work=[[Mid Day]]|date=2 July 2014|accessdate=15 February 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150215080505/http://www.mid-day.com/articles/aahana-kumras-dream-to-work-with-big-b-comes-true/15418176|archivedate=15 February 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/aahana-kumra-amitabh-bachchan-yudh-television-series/1/370866.html|title=She's a Scream: Newbie Aahana Kumra to make debut opposite Amitabh Bachchan in TV series Yudh|first=Suhani|last=Singh|work=[[India Today]]|date=11 July 2014|accessdate=15 February 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150215082130/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/aahana-kumra-amitabh-bachchan-yudh-television-series/1/370866.html|archivedate=15 February 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref> In 2017, Kumra had a leading role in the black comedy film ''[[Lipstick Under My Burkha]]'' as Leela.<ref name=lipstick>{{cite web|url=https://www.thequint.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/movie-review-lipstick-under-my-burkha|title=Movie Review: \u2018Lipstick Under My Burkha\u2019 Could Start A Revolution|website=thequint.com|accessdate=6 April 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180406122155/https://www.thequint.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/movie-review-lipstick-under-my-burkha|archivedate=6 April 2018|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The following year she portrayed the role of [[Priyanka Gandhi]] in the political biography film ''[[The Accidental Prime Minister (film)|The Accidental Prime Minister]].<ref name=accidental>{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/anupam-kher-the-accidental-prime-minister-first-look-5124144/lite/|title=Anupam Kher starts shooting for Manmohan Singh movie The Accidental Prime Minister, see photos|date=5 April 2018|website=indianexpress.com|accessdate=6 April 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180405082542/http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/anupam-kher-the-accidental-prime-minister-first-look-5124144/lite/|archivedate=5 April 2018|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Role !! Notes \n|-\n| 2009 || ''Mai'' || Tisha || Short Film \n|-\n| 2009 || ''[[Bollywood Hero]]'' || Clapper Girl || TV Series \n|-\n|2010|| ''Cardboard Thoughts'' || || Short Film\n|-\n| 2013 || ''[[Sona Spa]]'' || Ritu || Feature Film <ref>{{cite web|url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/bollywood/watch-trailer-of-naseeruddin-shahs-new-concept-thriller-film-sona-spa_128554.html|title=WATCH: Trailer of Naseeruddin Shah\u2019s new concept thriller film \u2018Sona Spa\u2019|date=23 February 2013|website=india.com|accessdate=6 April 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140903073043/http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/bollywood/watch-trai